int a(int a,int b) => a+b

OOP=>Object Oriented Programming

1)Object:Any Entity which has own state and behaviour
ex:Pen,paper etc..

2)class:Collection of objects
ex:Human body

3)abstraction:Hiding internal details and showing functionalities
ex:Login page

4)encapsualtion:wrapping up of data or binding of data
ex:capsule

5)inheritance:when one object acquire all the properties and behaviour of parent
ex:father-son

6)polymorphism:Many Ways to perform anything
1)Method Overloading
2)Method Overriding








 
